HEADWORD: Bonnaz
<hw>Bon"naz</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of embroidery
made with a complicated sewing machine, said to have been originally
invented by a Frenchman of the name of <etsep>Bonnaz</etsep>. The work
is done either in freehand or by following a perforated
design.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bonne</ent>⟦br⟧
